You can generate Python code from JSON using various libraries and tools available in the Python ecosystem. Here are three popular libraries that you can use to generate Python code from JSON:

1. jsonschema2popo: This library generates Python classes from a JSON schema, and it supports various data types, including arrays and nested objects. You can easily install this library using pip:

   ```
   pip install jsonschema2popo
   ```

   Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates how to generate Python classes from a JSON schema using jsonschema2popo:

   ```
   import jsonschema2popo

   schema = {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
      "title": "Person",
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
         "firstName": {
            "type": "string"
         },
         "lastName": {
            "type": "string"
         },
         "age": {
            "type": "integer"
         },
         "address": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
               "street": {
                  "type": "string"
               },
               "city": {
                  "type": "string"
               },
               "state": {
                  "type": "string"
               }
            }
         }
      },
      "required": ["firstName", "lastName"]
   }

   classes = jsonschema2popo.popos_from_schema(schema)

   for cls in classes:
      print(cls.render())
   ```

   This code generates two Python classes (Person and Address) from the given JSON schema and prints the code to the console. You can use this generated code in your Python application to serialize and deserialize JSON data.

2. quicktype: quicktype is an online tool that generates Python classes, as well as code in various other programming languages, from sample JSON data. You can simply paste your JSON data into the quicktype interface and specify the target language and other options to generate the corresponding Python code.

3. Pydantic: Pydantic is a library that provides data validation and settings management using Python type annotations. While Pydantic is not dedicated to generating Python code from JSON, it is a useful tool for working with JSON in Python. It automatically generates Python classes from Python types and has built-in support for JSON serialization and deserialization.

